Malt brand, Maltina, has said that it plans to treat families to a weekend long Easter celebration in Lagos on the 15th, through 18th April, 2022. According to a statement by the company, the Easter celebration would be held in conjunction with the Easter Hippity Hoppity ‘BunnyLand’ at Eko Hotels and Suites. It will feature an exciting collection of interesting fun games, children’s activities and spectacular night events lined up to make the 2022 Easter celebration a truly remarkable one for attendees. The statement said in part; “From the Bunny Land themed Park for children to the Good Friday BBQ Dinner, the Outdoor Theater Performance themed ‘Dreams Come Alive’, the Easter weekend fun fest is packed back-to-back with thrilling events and activities that will have the entire family bustling with excitement.” “Everyone can look forward to having a bunnyload of fun, bonding time and laughter with the bunny’lympics themed games session, a variety night featuring choice Chinese, Mexican and African food and the sensational $10 concert for the grownups.” Speaking on the upcoming celebration, Maltina Senior Brand Manager, Elohor Olumide-Awe, said “In line with our brand’s foremost value of sharing happiness, we at Maltina are geared to once again give families an unforgettable experience this Easter.”   Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com